96/*******************************************************************************
97 *
98 * FUNCTION: AcpiAhMatchUuid
99 *
100 * PARAMETERS: Data - Data buffer containing a UUID
101 *
102 * RETURN: ASCII description string for the UUID if it is found.
103 *
104 * DESCRIPTION: Returns a description string for "known" UUIDs, which are
105 * are UUIDs that are related to ACPI in some way.
106 *
107 ******************************************************************************/
108
109const char *
110AcpiAhMatchUuid (
111 UINT8 *Data)
112{
113 const AH_UUID *Info;
114 UINT8 UuidBuffer[UUID_BUFFER_LENGTH];
115
116
117 /* Walk the table of known ACPI-related UUIDs */
118
119 for (Info = Gbl_AcpiUuids; Info->Description; Info++)
120 {
121 /* Null string means description is a UUID class */
122
123 if (!Info->String)
124 {
125 continue;
126 }
127
128 AcpiUtConvertStringToUuid (Info->String, UuidBuffer);
129
130 if (!memcmp (Data, UuidBuffer, UUID_BUFFER_LENGTH))
131 {
132 return (Info->Description);
133 }
134 }
135
136 return (NULL);
137}
